JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s chances of avoiding a credit rating downgrade will be boosted by recent wage agreement between mine workers and the platinum sector&#8217;s largest producers, ratings firm Moody&#8217;s said on Monday.&#8220;The agreement is credit positive for both South Africa and platinum mining companies because it avoids a strike and the loss of platinum production,&#8221; the agency said in a credit analysis.Moody&#8217;s rates South Africa&#8217;s debt at Baa2, two notches above sub-investment grade, with a negative outlook, and it is due to make its next ratings decision by the end of November.